d, the knight sitting next to him.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“New knights, a mixture of squires and men at arms who have been pushed out of their territory.” Sir Gerald said. His voice was deep and monotone. Anon had never heard any inflection in his voice.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“How many are there?”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Enough to double our numbers.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">That would make damn near 40 knights, Anon noted. “But squires?” He inquired.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Yeah. Some haven’t run the Gauntlet yet. I guess Griffon plans to try them another way.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Another way? How you think he’s gonna do it?” </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">Gerald thought about that for a moment, his gaunt face deep in thought. “I honestly have no idea. He’ll be here sometime tonight, you should ask him.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“I’ll have to.” Anon gulped his beer down and crushed the can then stood up. “The Stablemaster get that package I ordered?”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“I think so, check in the back.” Anon started to move into the garage but Gerald stopped him. “Oh and that one new guy, Loop, that guy you brought in. Did he really make it to four?”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">“Yep,” Anon nodded.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&nbsp;</div></li><li class="li1"><di