Anon walked down the hall, his thoughts jumbled and confused. He opened his door and walked into his room. It felt like he was looking through the eyes of a stranger as he undressed. He laid down on the bed and pulled the blanket over him.

She had kissed him. How long had it been since he had a woman fall for him? At least a year. His last attempt had crashed and burned after it got off the ground. He refused to tell her about his nightly habits and wouldn’t change them. Hard to build a relationship if everyone thinks you’re cheating on them. But Claire…

Claire lived with him. They got along so far and she already knew his night job. But did she know him? He hadn’t even told her his name. Sure she probably knew it just from looking at the mail and papers he had, but he hadn’t told her. It wouldn’t work. Would it?

He turned over, still feeling her lips. “”Michael, you stupid fucking idiot.” He told himself. 

